Anonforce

Target IP: 10.10.30.166

Scanning



There are two TCP ports open on the target machine: FTP and SSH. The FTP application allows anonymous login.

Enumeration

Port 21: FTP

There is an interesting directory called notread. This directory contains two files: backup.pgp and private.asc. I downloaded these files on my local machine.


I used john to obtain the passphrase for the key which is xbox360. Using this passphrase, I should be able to decrypt the backup.pgp.


I decrypted the backup.pgp file using the key and obtained the shadow file. This file contains the password hash of two users: root and melodias.


I copied the two hashes in a text file called pass and then ran john on it.


I cracked the password of the user root using john, which is hikari.

Exploitation & Flags


Using the credential root:hikari, I gained access to the SSH application. Now I have a root SSH access on the target machine.


The two flag contents are shown above. The user.txt flag can be obtained using the anonymous FTP login.
